    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** (79.09) and **Mickey Moniak** (75.97) stand out as our primary engines. **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** benefits from a soft matchup against Jack Kochanowicz, and while the opposing catcher\u2019s pop time slightly suppresses his stolen base floor, the favorable park shift and high-skill matchup make him a locked-in core play. **Mickey Moniak** is this morning's biggest riser; despite being a projected #3 hitter against Spencer Arrighetti, he boasts a massive +14% platoon advantage and a +6% order bonus, further bolstered by the pitcher\u2019s slow delivery, which projects as a gold mine for our stolen base-starved categories. Similarly, **Josh Naylor** (74.14) and **Tyler Soderstrom** (71.06) are set up for high-leverage production against favorable pitching, with **Tyler Soderstrom** specifically benefiting from a +10% park factor that pushes his efficiency well into the \"Strong\" category.\n\nOur most difficult bench decision involved **Brice Turang**, who fell just short with a 54.21 score. Despite a top-third lineup slot, the combination of a daunting matchup against Dylan Cease and a negative SP skill impact kept him sidelined in favor of more efficient platoon-advantaged bats like **Vinnie Pasquantino** (63.50), who remains a critical utility piece due to his +14% dynamic platoon edge against Flaherty. We are also closely monitoring the weather situation for **James Wood**; although he possesses an elite #1 order position, his 53.50 score\u2014hampered by a tough matchup against Montgomery and a 37% rain risk\u2014made him the odd man out. We continue to hold **Gabriel Moreno**, **Carson Williams**, **Zach McKinstry**, **Kyle Karros**, **Alex Freeland**, and **Travis Bazzana** in reserve, prioritizing today\u2019s specific park and platoon advantages to maximize our limited games cap.\n\nFinally, keep a close eye on the catchers; **Dalton Rushing** (54.06) and **Luis Campusano** (49.43) are in \"Marginal\" territory, and both are currently flagged with \"Lineup Pending\" status. While we expect them to start, their lower-order placement significantly drags down their efficiency. **Corbin Carroll** remains our X-factor; despite facing a difficult arm in Bradish, his +16% park factor, wind-aided upside, and strong xwOBA suggest he can easily outperform his 71.79 score. We are betting heavily on these platoon-favorable dynamics to bridge the gap in HR and SB production tonight.",
